What is JavaScript?

JavaScript is a light-weight, cross-platform,
object-oriented programming languagee.
light-weight means that it does not take a lot of memory 
to run the code.
cross-platform that it can be run on different platforms.
object-oriented means that it is based on object-oriented
programming concepts.

Together with the HTML and CSS JavaScript is one of the 
3 core technologies of web development.

HTML is used to show content on a web page.
CSS is used to add styles to that content and handling the layout. In other words it handles the presentation.
JavaScript is used to add interactivity and dynamic effects to that content.